Minister Baird Says Canada’s Next Parliament to Resume Sitting on June 2

-- B y   I l a n   K o l e t
-- 
2011-05-16T18:39:13Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-05-16/minister-baird-says-canada-s-next-parliament-to-resume-sitting-on-june-2.html
Canada’s House of Commons will resume
sitting on June 2,  John Baird , the Canadian government’s House
Leader, said today.  The newly-elected members of parliament will elect a
speaker on June 2, and Stephen Harper’s Conservative government
will outline its priorities in a so-called Speech from the
Throne on June 3, Baird said, speaking to reporters in Ottawa.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Ilan Kolet in Ottawa at 
 ikolet@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Paul Badertscher at 
 pbadertscher@bloomberg.net  